gs) publish their latest headlines in feeds, using a number of standardized XML-based formats. For more information, see the online handbook entry for <a href=\"@aggregator-module\">Aggregator module</a>.','','none'),(3496,'','default','Viewing feeds','','none'),(3497,'','default','Feeds contain published content, and may be grouped in categories, generally by topic. Users view feed content in the <a href=\"@aggregator\">main aggregator display</a>, or by <a href=\"@aggregator-sources\">their source</a> (usually via an RSS feed reader). The most recent content in a feed or category can be displayed as a block through the <a href=\"@admin-block\">Blocks administration page</a>.','','none'),(3498,'','default','Adding, editing, and deleting feeds','','none'),(3499,'','default','Administrators can add, edit, and delete feeds, and choose how often to check each feed for newly updated items on the <a href=\"@feededit\">Feed aggregator administration page</a>.','','none'),(3500,'','default','OPML integration','','none'),(3501,'','default','A <a href=\"@aggregator-opml\">machine-readable OPML file</a> of all feeds is available. OPML is an XML-based file format used to share outline-structured information such as a list of RSS feeds. Feeds can also be <a href=\"@import-opml\">imported via an OPML file</a>.','','none'),(3502,'','default','Configuring cron','','none'),(3503,'','default','A correctly configured <a href=\"@cron\">cron maintenance task</a> is required to update feeds automatically.','','none'),(3504,'','default','<acronym title=\"Outline Processor Markup Language\">OPML</acronym> is an XML format used to exchange multiple feeds between aggregators. A single OPML document may contain a collection of many feeds. Drupal can parse such a file and import all feeds at once, saving you the effort of adding them manually. You may either upload a local file from your computer or enter a URL where Drupal can download it.','','none'),(3505,'','default','Administer news feed